CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. 9 reads: "Cashiers' Stand - Busy cashiers Celeste Schultz, left, and Arlene Holmes are but a part of the integrated staff at Treasure Island, new shopping center and self-service department store at Larimer and Broad in East Liberty. The store offers free parking, and is open Monday through Saturday from 10 A.M. until 10 P.M. - Harris Photo. - Adv. "
TitMainTitle: Man and woman wearing striped jackets, straightening display merchandise in Treasure Island department store, East Liberty
